  "title": "Geotechnical Engineer",
  "description": "<p>Job Description & Requirements</p><ul><li>Liaise with client and develop design concepts and basis of design to set direction of design.</li><li>Check engineering deliverables and assure technical integrity of design.</li><li>Ensure all engineering works comply with all relevant Statutory standards, Regulations and Codes of Practices.</li><li>Carry out various types of geotechnical design and analysis – deep excavations,  shafts, tunnels, slopes, foundations, etc.</li><li>Carry out appropriate design of structural nature where required.</li><li>Highlight technical issues and update Construction Department on changes and distribute to vendors, engineers and supervisors.</li><li>Plan and execute geotechnical and instrumentation installation and monitoring works.</li><li>Site evaluation of soil, rock, fault distribution and geological studies on site to determine their engineering properties.</li><li>Performs\n     other duties or projects as assigned.</li><li>Minimum\n     a Diploma, Degree in Geology or its equivalent.</li><li>Preferably\n     with a minimum of 5 years of relevant working experiences in construction\n     industry.</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Office, AutoCAD and Geotechnical analysis software.</li><li>Able to communicate effectively with Client, Consultants, Management and Subcontractors.</li></ul>",
